						<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d8e13f2525fe089da440c432b59e49c0?s=74&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-74 photo' height='74' width='74' />						<b class="fn"><a href='http://amourchaleur.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Dayna</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://ottodestruct.com/blog/2008/wordpress-27-comments-enhancements/comment-page-5/#comment-978">
							<time datetime="2009-03-31T22:50:03+00:00">
								March 31, 2009 at 10:50 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Yup, I did used the callback function for my comments.</p>
<p>You got it right. My &#8216;div-comment&#8217; in this comment_reply_link was incorrect. I didn&#8217;t specify which div id.</p>
<p>Thank you so much for your help. I have manage to get it working correctly on my site already. <img src="http://ottodestruct.com/wp-content/plugins/classic-smilies/img/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

